ir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104byx1665702617512.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/byx1665702617512.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/byx1665702617512.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"byx1665702617512\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Determines whether <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ugetname</span> adds the application name to the return\n    value.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"byx1665702617512__topic_d147056e1_d147057e1_d147058e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"byx1665702617512__p_d147059e1_d147060e1_d147061e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">UGETNAME_NoApplicationName</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section table\" id=\"byx1665702617512__section_w19ab1b5b3_w20ab1b5_w21ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"byx1665702617512__table_d18038e1_d18039e1_d18040e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">File section</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yzj1665702614359.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yzj1665702614359.html\" title=\"The [upi] section of the initialization file determines the appearance or behavior of many Universal Presentation Interface (UPI) objects under Microsoft Windows.\">[upi]</a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"byx1665702617512__section_lnf_5nh_zvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d301114e109\">Description</h2>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"byx1665702617512__note_nq5_5nh_zvb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Use this setting only if you expect\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ugetname</span> to return the name of the object without the application\n        name.</div>\n<p class=\"p\">By default, the application name is appended to the result returned by\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ugetname</span>. However, some versions of Uniface 9 did not return the\n        application name. If your 3GL application relies on this incompatible behavior, you can use\n        this switch to ensure that it works as you expect it to.</p>\n</section>\n<div class=\"example\" id=\"byx1665702617512__example_h22_wnh_zvb\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"byx1665702617512__pre_i22_wnh_zvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[upi]\nUGETNAME_NoApplicationName=1</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iwm1665703132785.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ugetname</a><p>Return the name of the Windows object associated with a window handle.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526317\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526317\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "UGETNAME_NoApplicationName Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 28, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Determines whether ugetname adds the application name to the return value. UGETNAME_NoApplicationName = 0 | 1 Default value 0 File section [upi] Description Note: Use this setting only if you expect ugetname to return the name of the object without the application name. By default, the application name is appended to the result returned by ugetname . However, some versions of Uniface 9 did not return the application name. If your 3GL application relies on this incompatible behavior, you can use this switch to ensure that it works as you expect it to. [upi] UGETNAME_NoApplicationName=1 Copy Related Links ugetname Return the name of the Windows object associated with a window handle. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}